<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1899-10-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1899-10-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="985" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d985">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Peirce</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Embassy
                                        of the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">St.
                                        Petersburg</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1899-10-27"><hi rend="italic">October 27,
                                1899</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 133.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                            receipt of your telegram<note n="1" xml:id="d985fn1">Printed
                                ante.</note> of the 26th instant, a copy of which I append upon the
                            overleaf.</p>
                        <p>Acting upon the instructions therein contained, I have requested a
                            further interview with Professor de Martens for the purpose of urging
                            upon him the wishes of our Government that the phrase “and the spirit of
                            international agreements bearing upon the subject” be omitted from the
                            protocol of the arbitration of the claims of American citizens arising
                            out of seizures of American vessels.</p>
                        <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Herbert H. D.
                            Peirce.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>